Good day,

Under certain circumstances (still yet to be determined), the
deepnano autopkgtest used to crash in timeout.  This led to a
ban of the package on CI infrastructure.  When trying to bring
the package back into adequate shape to allow for lifting the
ban, I noticed that said autopkgtest was raising a number of
failures worth RC bugs.  I fixed those so the software should be
usable again in time for bookworm.

Otherwise, deepnano autopkgtest now has some safeguards against
hoging a Debian CI slot for the maximum duration of the timeout,
which should be sufficient to address #921566 hopefully.

Have a nice day,  :)
